values: finally! a new post.. eheeheh! i havent posted in a long time. its not cos im busy or anything.. actually, i was anything but busy during the whole summer. i was jus plain lazy... ok, im getting lazy again. ill update some other time. its usually when insomnia strikes so i hope it does bfore school starts or else i wont be allowed on the comp anymore. nyerk.. heheh!

after grad:
went to carm's house.. ate uber yummy food (thanks tita louie)... bummed out with my exbatchmates outside the house and pretended that carm's house and all the decors are boracay cos i didnt go.. boohoo... then, when my dad picked me up at around 12:30 am, he and i went for ice cream at mcdo and we bonded til abt 2am... it was tiring but fun!

then, the day after grad.. i woke up at around 11am and an hour and a half later, i left to meet margie, gela,jocel,amanda,nikki,pat,yoti,fran and tif at vivere for aisa's surprise bday party. it was so much fun! when i got to room 2807, there were pink balloons everywhere and tita tet (tita aisa to margie) greeted me with her videocam. nikki, pat, and jocel were all on top of chairs hanging up those long stringy pink and white thingies on the wall. gela was jus acting all kinky everywhere and entertaining everyone with all her funny side comments. after the decors were all set up, we then blackmailed aisa on camera! heehee! hopefully, she hasnt watched it yet.... all the secrets that her friends spilled out! tsk tsk tsk... what kind of friends are you?!?! i almost ruined the surprise though cos when they were outside the hotel room door, i suddenly screamed out "surprise!" thinking that her brother was joking and that it was really the BELLBOY! hehe! good thing she didnt hear! the cake was really good and the pool was really really cold.. hehe stupid idea but really fun cos we sprouted b**bs in the water! hahaha! gela's mosquito bites were perky! haha jk besfren! but the funnest part of the night was murder mystery! damn you bo! why the hell did u hav to be french!? i was so into the character but it was only the accent that kept me from giving a superb performance! rar!! amanda was a great clair voyant though and gela really had me fooled.. she could really pass for a slut! hahah gawsh bfren... i dont know why but i jus adore teasing u! rocco was such a schizo.. sometimes with an accent, then mawawala! ano ba tlaga?! har har! neke.. i mean, marco was such a lllooozzzeeerrr (that was supposed to be said in a french accent)! my darling angel was such a trraitor! she accused me of being the murderer! though i really was the murderer.. waheheh!! and mama rosa....... happy birthday! hahahah!

..im not done yet...

i finally finished da vinci code...im wondering.. why is it banned from woodrose? it doesnt necessarily say bad stuff abt opus dei rite? sure, it showed that the albino did corporal mortification but for me, thats the only bad thing they showed about opus dei. also, in the book, i think the role of the church was misunderstood. at first, i thot that the church (or at least, opus dei) was behind the killings but then in the latter part of the book, i realized that the bishop and the albino were sort of tricked rite? correct me if im wrong cos i didnt really read-read it.. hehe i started the week bfore exams and continued it two weeks after so im kinda lost now... i think im gonna go and read it again.. haha!

here i am agen.. with nothing to do.. nothing in my brain.. ive had one of the most boring phone calls of my life! i was sitting there, on the phone and not talking.. i resorted to listening to the radio and waiting for my friend to talk to me about something. when i realized that nothing was gonna happen, i tried starting another conversation but all my friend answered was "ah ok" or "ah yeah" or "oh.. pake ko? (in a non-joking way)".. i cant believe i even tolerated that. if the better me was on the phone awhile ago, i wouldve put it down earlier. i was just ticked off cos i can't talk about anything with this friend anymore without thinking about what his/her reaction. i just really don't like it when people don't listen when i talk because i genuinely listen when they do. i mean, its alrite with me if people make me "bara" or joke around with things i say cos i sometimes enjoy that. i just don't like feeling that people don't care when i talk about some things and then expect me to listen and care for the things they have to say. to be really honest, i really don't enjoy talking to this friend anymore. i feel like he/she doesnt listen, doesnt care and all he/she cares about is him/herself.. the whole time i was talking to this friend, i was wishing that i was talking to someone else.. now, i feel like ive jus wasted 2-3 hours of my time.. 

i have a new favorite movie: finding neverland.. hehe i found it really nice and entertaining because of all the visual effects and the colors in the movie. i remembered how much i loved peter pan too. hehe when i was little, id pretend to be wendy and my life-sized (well, it was life sized for me that time--i was around 4-5) pink panther doll would be peter pan. haha! pathetic i know but i didnt hav any other playmates.. gem was too small so she was practically useless.. haha!

Growing up, Beethoven endured
mental/physical abuse by his demanding and

i watched let the love begin yesterday.. guess with whom?? haha i watched with SAM (Santiago, hinde Cruz!haha!), Boobies and Gonzi... laftrip todo.. sam was so kilig! hahahah! pucha, that movie sucked big time. the only funny ones there were tuesday vargas and bearwin! it was the typical cliche filipino movie... poor guy/rich girl.. goes abroad then meets when one comes back... then blah blah blah... we were literally guessing every scene. gawsh.. we really have to fix the movie industry of this country. let's stop all those cliche lovey dovey stories that are super cheesy! pinaka-panira in the movie is the ending!! arghh.. t was so irritating that i really wished i could turn back time and just watched phantom instead! hehehe whats up with the friggin' butterflies and the rain!? they kiss in front of the airport then all of a sudden, a crowd of butterflies come swarming towards them... then, the bad part's not done yet. after the huge, swarming butterflies (they prob used the butterflies para pa-romantic effect but it just doesnt click dammet!!! they shudve been more practical..), it suddenly rained!! WHAT!?!?! whats with the rain!? and it didnt drizzle ha.. it poured! i also noticed that on the mejo right side of the screen, the rain was less intense. oh oh.. another pang-asar pa.. after they kissed under the rain, they put their arms up as if theyve just won in some olympic game! its soo not romantic... dammet.. this makes me want to go into the movie-making business more! i wanna make movies that are so much different than the crap that theyre making us watch now...... if Richard Gutierrez wasnt cute there, i wudve stepped rite out and thrown my popcorn at the screen! hahah ... oh, and Angel Locsin was fat ha! huever's planning on watching that movie-- dont na.. watch something else.. like dreamboy.. JK!! haha
